Brachypeplus planus
Erichson, 1842: 149


: TAS, Van Diemen's Land;

caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 19.

Brachypeplus planus

, orig. A, B, C: male from TAS (“…Mt. Field West…”); 
A
: body, dorsal; 
B
: shoulder part of elytron, dorsal; 
C
: head and thorax, ventral; D-G: male from Tasmania (“…Mt. Field N. P…”); 
D
: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
E
: tegmen, ventral; 
F
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
G
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; 
H
: female from Tasmania (“…Lower Bardon R…”); ovipositor, ventral. Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Fig. A; 
b
= 1.0 mm to Fig. B; 
с
= 0.5 mm to Fig. C; 
d
= 0.25 mm to Figs D–H.
